reviews.review:
Very mundane. Writing was very bad - seems like first time screenwriters. Acting was mediocre.  Only redeeming quality was the special effects, but ALL movies have good special effects now.

Would have liked to wait till Video.. DVD RENTAL!... ugh. what a waste of time.
It is the great movie to watch and I am a big Star Wars fan.
Very fun movie. Great finish for the franchise. It's not perfect, but it is satisfying. I think it will get better the more i watch it.
Do not listen to the critics. This movie is amazing, a true Star Wars movie.

None of the nine movies are perfect (stormtroopers still can’t shoot!!!), but if this has to end, this is a fitting tribute to the franchise, probably the most suspenseful and gut wrenching of the lot. I’d give it 5 stars, but I’m still pissed Kylo killed Han )
ridiculous hodge podge of a story line. No character development, no explanations,  and a mess of an ending. This has nothing to do with the original SW movies, it felt like being suckered.

Do not listen to any of the critics reviews. If you're a Star Wars fan I think you'll be thoroughly impressed. 

If you wanted to change Star Wars instead of creating your own new franchise then yeah you may not like it. 

You can easily enjoy TLJ and RoS or you could hate TLJ and love RoS. It's been made in such a way that it accounts for TLJ but it doesn't depend on it in anyway. Nothing really happened in TLJ that permanently impacted anything other than Luke's disappearance and his ultimate fate. 

So just go and see it. If you love Star Wars you'll enjoy this movie.
Don’t get me wrong. I love Star Wars. But this is the worst film of the entire 42 year saga. The story made no sense characters when against logic.

Saw Rise last night, I honestly do not get what the critics are saying.  It does everything we want from a movie, action, nostalgia, fan service. cameos and adventure. Enough twists and turns to keep the story moving. Absolutely loved it. A great way to end a 42 year old journey.

I enjoyed this film. I’m over this era of over-analyzing every film that comes out like it needs to be a gosh darn masterpiece. Here’s a news flash: Star Wars as a whole are NOT cinematic works of art to be compared with the likes of Casablanca and Good Will Hunting. They’re silly space-action films with questionable dialogue and fun space scenes. Just go to the film and enjoy it instead of launching an investigative analysis into a series made for children.
